The level of inbreeding and madness among the Targaryen dynasty has been grossly overstated by fandom and especially by the TV show Their detailed family tree in TWOIAF struck me by how LITTLE inbreeding and madness actualy occurred relative to what everyone thinks Interestingly Daenerys s parents the mad King Aerys II and his sister wife Queen Rhaella were themselves the st in the family born of an incestuous union in over years or thereabouts I have always thought that the madness situation has less to do with genetics and more to do with the extremely potent and perilous power of the Dragonlord lineage to which the Targaryens belong It seems that when madness occurs the afflicted person quite literally takes on the most terrifying characteristics of a dragon with an obsession with power violence and fire And even more fascinating those who do go mad are almost all male not female

The thing with the Hound is that to complete his character arch he has to die Which sucks But it makes his character even stronger Building a character in a movie tv show or a video game that people care for isn t easy But with Sandor they did the best job I ve ever seen A character we were almost forced to hate and despise Bc of the side he was on But we spent more time with him throughout the show We saw who he truly was And we saw him become in some ways good This causes a deeper impact a deeper connection with the character Because a character arch like this is something most people can relate to Especially when he helps Sansa and Arya We place ourselves in the girl s shoes Bc we too have had teachers Sometimes we didn t always see what they were teaching us but eventually when we do we appreciate them That was Sandor to Arya and Sansa A teacher Whom they didn t realize had good intentions and truly wanted to help them But now they do see that side of him And so do we as an audience We ve related to him and now we care about him most of us do And the final act to truly make his character arch complete is death We ve all lost someone who was like a teacher to us Whether that be a grandparent a parent or a mentor to us We ve experienced loss We ve lost someone we ve cared for And how they ve built up Sandor so far is very similar We care about him we want the best for him But in the end we are gonna feel actual pain when he dies Bc it s gonna feel like we actually lost a friend or a mentor Thus Sandor is an incredible character with an even better character arch

I finally got my Odyssey plus If it wasn t for your recommendation in another video to give it some time I might have returned it by now The two immediate things I found about it compared with my original Odyssey it s more comfortable I was initially concerned about all the extra space beneath the nose area and light leak but that really turned into a non issue when you re in VR However it really is not as sharp as the original Odyssey It appears to me that things you see in the distance is more blurry That really annoyed me at first but then I kept adjusting it and found that if I lower the headset as low as I could on the back of my head things get better After using it now for several hours of gaming it s really growing on me I am experiencing one issue with it in that every once in a while it picks up very loud noises in the speakers and I don t know why Ultimately the only way I got it to stop was a reboot I ll have to spend some time looking into that It doesn t happen with my original Odyssey so I m wondering about if it has something to do with the builtin Bluetooth I have to say the comfort level is greatly improved and so that really makes much of the difference as to why I m liking this new unit
